org.moeaframework.core

Class PopulationIO

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.moeaframework.core.PopulationIO

  • public class PopulationIO
extends java.lang.Object
    Collection of static methods for reading and writing populations to files. The write(java.io.File, java.lang.Iterable<org.moeaframework.core.Solution>) and read(java.io.File) methods should be used when storing and retrieving solutions to be used by this framework. The writeObjectives(java.io.File, java.lang.Iterable<org.moeaframework.core.Solution>) and readObjectives(java.io.BufferedReader) should be used when the data is accessed by external programs, as these two methods store the data in a human-readable form.
